	(text "2️⃣ High-Frequency (Decoupling) Capacitors\nWhat they do:\n\nKill switching spikes\n\nProvide instant current at MHz speeds\n\nReduce EMI\n\nKeep IC stable\n\nTypically:\n\n100nF (0.1µF)\n\n10nF sometimes\n\nX7R ceramic\n\nPlaced VERY close to IC pins\n\nThey respond well to:\n\nMHz range\n\nFast edge transitions\n\nSwitching noise"
